Got it 👍 — here’s how your **installation section** can look if you want to explicitly include the commands you just listed (`pkg upgrade && pkg update`, `pkg install curl`, `pkg install espeak`):

---

````markdown
## 📦 Installation Instructions (for Termux)

1. **Update and upgrade Termux packages**
   ```bash
   pkg update && pkg upgrade -y
````

2. **Install required packages**

   ```bash
   pkg install bash curl jq espeak termux-api python -y
   ```

   *(If you prefer step-by-step instead of all-in-one, you can also run:)*

   ```bash
   pkg install curl
   pkg install espeak
   ```

3. **Install Python dependency**

   ```bash
   pip install requests
   ```

4. **Clone the repository**

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/techvyana20-oss/jarvis-assistant.git
   cd jarvis-assistant
   ```

5. **Make the script executable**

   ```bash
   chmod +x jarvis.sh
   ```

6. **Run JARVIS**

   ```bash
   ./jarvis.sh
   ```

```



